Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 13:33:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ci-watch: add Cursor Automation prompt + helper poller for
 upstream CI

Adds .ci-watch/ tooling to monitor the upstream vllm-project/vllm-omni
CI from this fork, without relying on a long-lived process.

- automation-prompt.md: ready-to-paste prompt body and configuration
  steps for a Cursor Automation (Scheduled trigger). Each tick spins
  up a fresh Cloud Agent that diffs the upstream CI state against a
  baseline stored in a tracking GitHub Issue (label 'ci-watch') in
  this repository, and only comments when something changed. This is
  the recommended persistent-monitoring path since Cursor-hosted
  Cloud Agent VMs are not guaranteed to stay alive between turns.

- poll.sh: optional self-contained bash polling loop, useful only on
  long-lived hosts (My Machines worker, personal devbox, etc.).

- README.md: how the pieces fit together; how to switch the alert
  channel from a tracking issue to Slack/webhook; why this lives in
  the fork rather than upstream.

- .gitignore: excludes runtime artifacts (events.log, runner.log,
  state/).
